COPY public.blogs (id, title, slug, excerpt, content, cover_image_url, author, status, tags, featured, seo_title, seo_description, reading_time, created_by, updated_by, published_at, created_at, updated_at, categories, submitted_by, is_customer_submission, store_id) FROM stdin;
73bfed91-ee75-4cd5-a73a-85590f70e36f	Why Simple Nutrition Wins Every Time	why-simple-nutrition-wins-every-time	Good health doesn't require complicated diets. Discover how simple, sustainable nutrition habits can lead to better long-term health and wellness.	<p style="text-align:left">When it comes to health, many people believe they need complicated diets, expensive supplements, or strict meal plans to see results. In reality, good nutrition is often much simpler.</p><p>A balanced plate with vegetables, protein, whole grains, and healthy fats can provide most of the nutrients your body needs. Small habits such as drinking enough water, eating regular meals, and choosing home-cooked foods more often can have a bigger impact than following the latest diet trend.</p><p>The goal of nutrition should not be perfection. It should be building sustainable habits that fit your lifestyle and can be maintained for years. Consistency beats extremes every time.</p><p>At the end of the day, health isn't about doing more—it's about doing the basics well, day after day.</p><p></p>	https://oiblxqrvyekxdbimvhod.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/media/blog-covers/h8698183di_1781207185084.jpg	Vansh Gupta	published	{"Healthy Habits","Mindful Eating","Real Food",Protein,"Gut Health","Indian Food"}	t	Why Simple Nutrition Wins Every Time | Soakd	Discover why simple nutrition habits, balanced meals, and consistency are more effective for long-term health than restrictive diets.	1	bab29fff-0265-477a-9a7b-16f1af9007a6	bab29fff-0265-477a-9a7b-16f1af9007a6	2026-06-02 20:49:38.068+00	2026-06-02 20:49:38.31271+00	2026-06-24 13:28:44.747559+00	{"Healthy Living"}	\N	f	a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001
